The paper focuses on time series classification using shapelet transform, which is a common technique in machine learning and falls under the category of supervised learning. The paper proposes two strategies to reduce the time complexity of the ensemble shapelet transform algorithm. These strategies involve selecting shapelet candidates of a given small length and training a single linear classifier in the feature space. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the following arXiv CS sub-categories: 

- cs.LG (Machine Learning): This sub-category covers research on various machine learning techniques, including supervised learning, which is the focus of this paper. 
- cs.DM (Data Mining): This sub-category covers research on the process of discovering patterns in large datasets, which is relevant to the time series classification problem addressed in this paper. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): This sub-category covers research on various aspects of artificial intelligence, including machine learning, which is the focus of this paper. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): This sub-category covers research on various computer vision and pattern recognition techniques, which may be relevant to the time series classification problem addressed in this paper. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): This sub-category covers research on various neural network and evolutionary computing techniques, which may be relevant to the machine learning techniques used in this paper.
